<BODY>
<HEADLINE> McGwire Hits 534 Homer, Ties Foxx  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   SAN FRANCISCO (AP) -- Mark McGwire hit his NL-leading 12th homer
of the season Monday night and moved into a tie with Jimmie Foxx
for ninth place on the career list with 534.
</P>
<P>
   McGwire's solo homer off San Francisco starter Livan Hernandez
came in the sixth inning and went 430 feet into the right-center
bleachers. McGwire has homered in nine of his last 14 games.
</P>
<P>
   It was the first run of the game for the St. Louis Cardinals,
and broke a 26-inning scoreless streak by Giants pitchers -- San
Francisco's longest such streak since a 30-inning scoreless run on
July 5-9, 1988.
</P>
<P>
   Mickey Mantle is eighth on the career homer list with 536.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
