<HEADLINE> Rundown Of Maple Leafs' Shots  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   EAST RUTHERFORD, N.J. (AP) -- A run-down of the Toronto Maple
Leafs' NHL modern-era record-low six shots in their 3-0 loss to the
New Jersey Devils on Monday night:
</P>
<P>
   First Period -- Three shots. Igor Korolev had the Maple Leafs'
best chance with a back-hander in close at 7:35, which was stopped
by Devils goalie Martin Brodeur. Sergei Berezin had the other two
shots in the period, including one from the center red line with
1:47 remaining.
</P>
<P>
   Second Period -- Two shots. Berezin and Steve Thomas.
</P>
<P>
   Third Period -- One shot. Darcy Tucker had a short-handed chance
in the opening two minutes.
</P>
</TEXT>
