<DATE_TIME> 2000-05-09 01:57 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Astros' Lima To Miss Start  </HEADLINE>
By MICHAEL A. LUTZ, AP Sports Writer
<TEXT>
<P>
   HOUSTON (AP) -- Jose Lima, looking nothing like the pitcher who
won 21 games last season for the Houston Astros, will get extra
time to prepare for his next outing.
</P>
<P>
   ''We're going to skip Lima's next start,'' Astros manager Larry
Dierker said Monday night.
</P>
<P>
   ''I think we'll pitch him Tuesday in Milwaukee. We have an
off-day and this will give him a chance to have two or three
bullpen sessions so he can try to get his problems ironed out.''
</P>
<P>
   Lima is 1-5 with a 9.53 ERA in seven starts. He has allowed a
major league-leading 16 home runs in only 39 2-3 innings, along
with 65 hits.
</P>
<P>
   Lima got a no-decision Sunday night in Los Angeles despite
another shaky outing. The All-Star righty was charged with seven
runs -- four earned -- and six hits in four innings.
</P>
<P>
   Last year, Lima was 21-10 with a 3.58 ERA for the NL Central
champions. Now, he's lost five straight decisions.
</P>
<P>
   Lima's next start was supposed to come at home against
Cincinnati this weekend. He has struggled at new Enron Field, which
has been a homer haven so far.
</P>
<P>
   ''He's not that far off,'' Dierker said. ''He's just throwing
too many fat pitches. His velocity is good. We just want him to
work on a few things.''
</P>
<P>
   Lima wants to pitch himself out of the slump, but he accepts the
decision.
</P>
<P>
   ''I want to pitch, but I understand,'' he said after learning of
the move Monday night. ''No one is more frustrated by this than me.
I want to get it turned around and hopefully, this will help me.
I'd rather keep pitching, but I understand.''
</P>
<P>
   His teammates are rooting for him. They are concerned about
their animated pitcher, too.
</P>
<P>
   ''Jose will come to the park today and he'll be on the top step
of the dugout,'' third baseman Ken Caminiti said. ''With his antics
on the mound, you have to back it up. All the other teams are
digging in against him.''
</P>
<P>
   Caminiti repeated a theme that has recurred in analyzing Lima's
fall.
</P>
<P>
   ''Jose needs to pitch with his head and not his heart,''
Caminiti said. ''That's the way he is, but he has to learn to
control it.''
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
