<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Oakland's Giambi Brothers Homer  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   ANAHEIM, Calif. (AP) -- Jason and Jeremy Giambi hit home runs for
Oakland on Monday night, joining the rare set of brothers to
connect in the same game.
</P>
<P>
   Jason hit a two-run homer, his major league-leading 14th, in the
second inning against Anaheim. Jeremy hit a three-run shot in the
fourth, his second of the season, in a 9-8 loss.
</P>
<P>
   Vladimir and Wilton Guerrero were the previous brothers to homer
in the same game, doing it last Oct. 2 for Montreal.
</P>
<P>
   There was no definitive word from baseball on how many pairs of
brothers had accomplished the feat.
</P>
<P>
   Among the other duos to do it were Hank and Tommie Aaron, Paul
and Lloyd Waner, Billy and Tony Conigliaro, Graig and Jim Nettles,
Cal and Billy Ripken, Rick and Wes Farrell, Al and Tony Cuccinello,
Matty and Jesus Alou, and Aaron and Bret Boone.
</P>
</TEXT>
