   Some analysts expect to see the technology sector working to
recover some of Monday's big losses, as investor sentiment
continues to see-saw.
</P>
<P>
   Monday's session was the quietest trading day of the year, and
Tuesday doesn't figure to be much different.
</P>
<P>
   Market-watchers say many big money managers are keeping to the
sidelines with the Federal Reserve widely expected to boost
short-term interest rates a week from today.
</P>
<P>
   Bond prices are higher in early trading, but stocks are trading
mostly lower in Europe.
</P>
