<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Dow Up 62; Nasdaq Off 53  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- Stocks were mixed in quiet early trading today
as investors assessed the market for technology stocks after
Monday's sharp drop.
</P>
<P>
   In the first hour of trading on Wall Street, the Dow Jones
industrial average was up 62.38 at 10.666.01. The Nasdaq composite
index was off 53.39 at 3,615.99.
</P>
<P>
   Broader stock indicator were mixed. The Standard &AMP; Poor's 500
index was down 0.48 at 1,423.69.
</P>
<P>
   Cisco Systems, which was pummeled Monday following a negative
article in Barron's magazine, rose | today to 63 9/16. Other
high-tech stocks were mixed.
</P>
<P>
   With few major economic indicators coming out and the next
meeting of the Federal Reserve Board a week off, stock trading has
been slow in recent sessions. Monday was the quietest session of
the year so far.
</P>
<P>
   The Russell 2000 index was up 0.43 today at 500.51.
</P>
<P>
   Despite the gains in major stock indicators, declining issues
edged out advancing ones by a 4-to-3 margin on the New York Stock
Exchange, where volume came to 118.38 million shares, slightly
ahead of Tuesday's quiet levels.
</P>
<P>
   U.S. shares seemed to be shaking off weakness in overseas
markets. In Tokyo, the benchmark Nikkei stock average tumbled
355.42 points, or 1.95 percent, to close at 17,844.54 points, its
lowest level in six months.
</P>
<P>
   European stocks were also trading lower. In afternoon trading,
Germany's DAX index was down 1.4 percent, Britain's FT-SE 100 was
down 0.3 percent, and France's CAC-40 was down 1.5 percent.
</P>
<P>
   ------
</P>
<P>
   On the Net:
</P>
<P>
   New York Stock Exchange: http://www.nyse.com
</P>
<P>
   Nasdaq Stock Market: http://www.nasdaq.com
</P>
