<HEADLINE> Dollar Mostly Down, Gold Falls  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   LONDON (AP) -- The U.S. dollar was mostly lower against other
major currencies in trading today. Gold prices fell.
</P>
<P>
   The euro was quoted at 90.25 cents, up from 89.37 cents on
Monday. Later, in midday trading in New York, the euro traded at
90.62 cents.
</P>
<P>
   Other dollar rates in Europe, compared with late Monday,
included 109.52 Japanese yen, up from 108.93; 1.7209 Swiss francs,
down from 1.7336; 1.4938 Canadian dollars, up from 1.4918.
</P>
<P>
   The British pound was quoted at $1.5305, down from $1.5309.
</P>
<P>
   In midday trading in New York, the dollar bought 109.50 yen, and
the pound was worth $1.5320.
</P>
<P>
   Based on euro rates, the dollar is worth 2.1659 German marks,
down from 2.1872; 7.2650 French francs, down from 7.3398; 2.4407
Dutch guilders, down from 2.4658; 2,144.50 Italian lire, down from
2,166.58.
</P>
<P>
   London dealers fixed a recommended gold price of $276.80 per
ounce, down from the closing price of $277.70 bid Monday. In
Zurich, the bid price was $275.90, down from $277.10. Gold in Hong
Kong fell $1.00 to close at $276.95.
</P>
<P>
   Silver closed in London at $5.03 bid per troy ounce, up from
$5.00.
</P>
</TEXT>
