<HEADLINE> NYC First Lady Replaced in Play  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- Emmy-award winner Holland Taylor will replace
New York City first lady Donna Hanover in the off-Broadway play
''The Vagina Monologues.''
</P>
<P>
   Hanover, who was supposed to perform in the sexually suggestive
show beginning May 30, postponed her appearance last week, citing
family circumstances. She did not elaborate.
</P>
<P>
   Her husband, Republican Mayor Rudolph Giuliani, announced April
27 that he has prostate cancer.
</P>
<P>
   Taylor, 56, won an Emmy for best supporting actress last year
for her portrayal of a sexy middle-age judge in the TV show ''The
Practice.''
</P>
<P>
   The play consists of monologues delivered by three different
actresses and includes such frank topics as orgasms, pelvic exams,
sexual abuse, sexual fantasies and childbirth. Taylor will appear
with Kirstie Alley and Hazel Goodman.
</P>
