<HEADLINE> Playwright Tom Stoppard Honored  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   LONDON (AP) -- Playwright Tom Stoppard was one of four recipients
named Tuesday to join the Order of Merit, the highest personal
honor bestowed by the queen of England.
</P>
<P>
   Also receiving the honor were sculptor Sir Anthony Caro, Nobel
Prize-winning chemist Sir James Black and mathematician Sir Roger
Penrose.
</P>
<P>
   The Order of Merit, founded in 1902 by King Edward VII, is given
by the queen to individuals of exceptional distinction. Membership
is considered the queen's personal gift.
</P>
<P>
   Other members include former Prime Minister Margaret Thatcher,
actor Sir John Gielgud, opera singer Dame Joan Sutherland and Queen
Elizabeth II's husband, Prince Philip.
</P>
