<HEADLINE> AP Corrects Crime Story  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   WASHINGTON (AP) -- The Associated Press reported erroneously on
May 7 that there were 88 murders in Nashville, Tenn., according to
preliminary crime statistics released by the FBI.
</P>
<P>
   Nashville had 68 murders last year, compared with 97 in 1998.
</P>
