measure ''would be catastrophic, disastrous to American ...
products and services.'' Carter acknowledged that China has failed
to take adequate steps in terms of human rights, democracy and
labor standards. ''But ... a negative vote ... will be a serious
setback and impediment for the further democratization, freedom and
human rights in China,'' Carter said.
