purposes. The bill's sponsors cited students keeping journals for a
marketing survey and a technology firm that provided schools with
free computers and Internet access, but monitored students' online
activity. The Parent Teacher Association has endorsed the student
privacy proposal, but groups representing school administrators and
school board members have not.
</P>
