<HEADLINE> Critics Name Best Plays, Musicals  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   NEW YORK (AP) -- ''Jitney,'' August Wilson's drama about taxi-cab
drivers in 1970s Pittsburgh, was named best play, and ''James
Joyce's 'The Dead,'' based on the Irish author's famous short
story, was chosen as best musical Tuesday by the New York Drama
Critics' Circle.
</P>
<P>
   It was the seventh time Wilson, author of such plays as
''Fences'' and Ma Rainey's Black Bottom,'' has won a Drama Critics'
Circle award.
</P>
<P>
   ''Copenhagen,'' Michael Frayn's play about a mysterious meeting
between two physicists on opposing sides during World War II, was
picked as best foreign play. The Circle has the option of giving a
best foreign or best American play award, depending on what wins
the best-play prize.
</P>
</TEXT>
