<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Southern Portugal Has Power Outage  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   LISBON, Portugal (AP) -- A massive power outage late Tuesday
plunged the southern half of Portugal, including the capital
Lisbon, into darkness.
</P>
<P>
   The lights went out in Lisbon and along a 180-mile mostly rural
stretch to the Algarve coastal area around 10 p.m., according to
the national power company Electricidade de Portugal.
</P>
<P>
   The blackout ended in Lisbon after 1 hour 45 minutes but
emergency phone lines were jammed with calls.
</P>
<P>
   The power company's chief national engineer Hugo Assuncao told
state radio RDP that a technical fault occurred at a substation in
Rio Maior, 50 miles north of Lisbon, but he said the cause was not
known.
</P>
<P>
   Officials said there were no reports of serious injuries as a
result of the blackout.
</P>
</TEXT>
