<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Compaq To Invest $100M in S. Korea  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   SEOUL, South Korea (AP) -- Compaq Computer Corp. of the United
States said Wednesday it will invest $100 million in South Korean
Internet companies this year.
</P>
<P>
   The global computer maker said the money will be spent on
forming strategic alliances with Korean Internet service providers,
strengthening its service and consulting in the Internet area
through mergers and acquisitions or partnerships.
</P>
<P>
   It also said it will enhance e-commerce and electronic banking
activities in the country.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
